extends ui_layout

block content

  .ui.text.container
    br
    h2 Safe Self-Presentation Post-Activity Quiz
    form#pres_post.ui.reply.form(action='/postquiz/presentation', method='POST')
      input(type='hidden', name='_csrf', value=_csrf)
      .ui.form
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='phone_post') You have your phone out when your spills chocolate milk on his shirt. Do you...
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='phone_post', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label Neither, I don't want to embarrass my friend.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='phone_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Text your friends because they'll think it's funny.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='phone_post',  tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Take a picture and post so everyone can see.
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='disclose_post') Jin is looking for a partner for his English project. He wants to make a post about it where his classmates can see. What should he write?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='disclose_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label "I need a partner for my English project! Text me at 234-567-8901 if you'd like to work together.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='disclose_post', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label "I need a partner for my English project! Send me a private message if you want to work together."
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='disclose_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label "I need a partner for my English project! Here's a screenshot of my email address so you can contact me.""
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='picture_post') Anna's friend made a post about her on a social media site that was meant to be nice, but it actually makes her uncomfortable. What should Anna do?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='picture_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Make an embarrassing post about her as payback.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='picture_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Pretend nothing happened - everthing on social media goes away eventually.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='picture_post', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label Tell her friend to delete it, because it makes her uncomfortable.
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='lie_post') Jacob is jealous about his friends’ vacation pictures. He’s considering to lie about being in Japan for Summer break while he actually stayed home.  Should he do this?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='lie_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Yes, because it makes him feel better about himself.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='lie_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Yes, because it doesn't matter whether information on social media is true or not.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='lie_post', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label No, because someone could find out the truth and it would be embarrassing.
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='complain_post') Carlos and his friends make fun of their teachers and parents on social media sites that the adults don't go on. Are Carlos's conversations private?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='complain_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Yes, because the things you say on social media disappear after you send them.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='complain_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Yes, because Carlos kept the conversation between him and his friends.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='complain_post', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label No, because someone could take a screenshot or show a mean conversation to someone else.
        br
        h2 Just a few more questions... There are no right or wrong answers here!
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='like') How much did you like this activity?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='like', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label I didn't like it at all.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='like', tabindex='0', value='2')
            label Not very much, but it wasn't awful.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='like', tabindex='0', value='3')
            label A little bit, it was neither good nor bad.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='like', tabindex='0', value='4')
            label Some - it was god but not amazing.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='like', tabindex='0', value='5')
            label A lot - it was awesome!
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='friends') Would you recommend this activity to your friends?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='friends', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label No, not at all.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='friends', tabindex='0', value='2')
            label Maybe.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='friends', tabindex='0', value='3')
            label Yes, I would!
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='length') What did you think of the length of the activity?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='length', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label It was too short.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='length', tabindex='0', value='2')
            label It was just the right length.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='length', tabindex='0', value='3')
            label It was too long.
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='understand') Do you think you understand the issues of self-presentation better after completing the activity?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='understand', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label Yes, I understand the issues better.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='understand', tabindex='0', value='2')
            label I'm not sure.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='understand', tabindex='0', value='3')
            label No, I didn't learn anything.
        button.ui.button(type='submit') Submit
      br
      br
      br